"container-title":"Molecules","abstract":"Mushrooms are widely distributed around the world and are heavily consumed because of their nutritional value and medicinal properties. Polysaccharides (PSs) are an important component of mushrooms, a major factor in their bioactive properties, and have been intensively studied during the past two decades. Monosaccharide composition/combinations are important determinants of PS bioactivities. This review summarizes: (i) monosaccharide composition/combinations in various mushroom PSs, and their relationships with PS bioactivities; (ii) possible biosynthetic pathways of mushroom PSs and effects of key enzymes on monosaccharide composition; (iii) regulation strategies in PS biosynthesis, and prospects for controllable biosynthesis of PSs with enhanced bioactivities.","tags":["#literature_note"],"author":[{"family":"Wang","given":"Qiong","literal":""},{"family":"Wang","given":"Qiong","literal":""},{"family":"Wang","given":"Feng","literal":""},{"family":"Wang","given":"Feng","literal":""},{"family":"Xu","given":"Zhenghong","literal":""},{"family":"Xu","given":"Zhenghong","literal":""},{"family":"Xu","given":"Zhenghong","literal":""},{"family":"Ding","given":"Zhongyang","literal":""},{"family":"Ding","given":"Zhongyang","literal":""}],"citation-key":"wang_bioactive_2017","year":"2017","dateCreated":"2026-03-31","reading-status":"to-read","aliases":["Bioactive Mushroom Polysaccharides: A Review on Monosaccharide Composition, Biosynthesis and Regulation."],"author-links":["[[Author/Qiong Wang]]","[[Author/Qiong Wang]]","[[Author/Feng Wang]]","[[Author/Feng Wang]]","[[Author/Zhenghong Xu]]","[[Author/Zhenghong Xu]]","[[Author/Zhenghong Xu]]","[[Author/Zhongyang Ding]]","[[Author/Zhongyang Ding]]"],"attachment":["[[biblib/wang_bioactive_2017/wang_bioactive_2017.pdf|PDF]]"],"related":[[]]},"task_lines":[],"tasks":{},"codeblock_ranges":[],"last_embed":{"hash":"gbve9z","at":1774951888673}},"smart_blocks:Research/@wang_bioactive_2017.md#-